shared_text:
Grand Oaks Elementary School is at Grand Oaks Elementary.
11 hrs 路 Clinton, TN 路

As a school we took some time to stop and reflect on this Patriot Day. Starting at morning announcements we paused to think about and honor those who lost their lives 19 years ago. Many grade levels incorporated 9/11 research and response into their lessons today. Students across the school learned about what it means to be a hero and why we take the time to honor them. We honor those who serve on the front lines, as first responders, and those everyday heroes who step up in times of need. Throughout this somber day it becomes abundantly clear that the children in this building are the future. They have kind hearts and by taking the time to reflect on the past we hope to instill in them a passion for being part of a brighter tomorrow.

#NeverForget #EveryStudentEveryDay

Todays Album: https://photos.app.goo.gl/j9b8TuKjpbdgztkg8
Virtual parents if you got a picture of your child today please send it on Facebook messenger so we can add it to the album.

We will be continuing our celebration of colors this week by honoring Patriot Day on Friday. On Friday, we encourage all students and staff to wear red, white, and blue to honor and remember those impacted by 9/11/2001. Restrictions due to COVID-19 will prevent us from having our traditional Patriots Day ceremony. However, we still want to take the time to be united in our appreciation and respect for the heroes who make our country great. Please be on the lookout for more information tomorrow. Virtual students are encouraged to dress up as well. Please share your pictures to our page so we can include them in our album! #NeverForget #TogetherAtHeart

post_text:
Grand Oaks Elementary School is accepting applications for a Diagnostic Education Assistant.

This position is categorized as an Educational Assistant (EA) who works with Special Education students under the direction of a licensed teacher. The EA is engaged in all learning activities as directed by the teacher. All Educational Assistants employed by Anderson County Schools are required to be HQ.

Qualifications

A high school diploma is a minimum requirement. Some college is desired. The successful candidate must be Highly Qualified (HQ), as defined by federal law. The HQ status is achieved by either passing the Praxis Parapro Test, which assesses general knowledge; by having a minimum of an A.S. degree; or having successfully completed 48 semester hours of college work.

Apply at the below link: https://acsd.tedk12.com/hire/ViewJob.aspx?JobID=1664

Cadet Private Puleo also offered insight into her future at West Point. As her very busy schedule permits, Miss Puleo plans on dropping into the Drill & Ceremony classroom to provide nuggets of information on how to be successful in life!

post_text:
Norris Middle School is excited to announce Carey Downs as their new Vice Principal. Mrs. Downs brings multiple years of experience to her new position, including 8 years of teaching, and the honor of being named Teacher of the Year twice. She has served as the Curriculum Specialist at Lake City Middle since 2017. She also enjoyed being the ACHS Softball Coach from 2009-2012. An alumnus of UTC and Carson Newman, she holds a bachelors in Middle Grades Education with a Physical Education endorsement and a Masters in Instructional Leadership.
When she is not working, you will find Carey and her family (husband Ben and sons Josiah and Cooper) on the ballfield, near the lake, or singing Hamilton lyrics. In addition, she loves to read (she is a lifelong fan of Harry Potter) and enjoys participating in outdoor activities in her spare time.

post_text:
Attention Parents: Make sure to check the following dates to make sure your student(s) comes to school on the correct day. This year due to all of changes due to COVID-19 we are implementing a staggered start to help students and staff to adjust to all of the new changes.

Kindergarten - 2 week staggered return to adequately teach health and safety procedures and routines (8/10-8/21; will begin full-time week of 8/24)

1st Grade - 1 week staggered return to adequately teach health and safety procedures and routines (8/10-8/14; will begin full-time week of 8/17)

2nd Grade - Monday (8/10)

3rd Grade - Tuesday (8/11)

4th Grade - Wednesday (8/12)

5th Grade - Wednesday (8/12)

2nd - 5th - all will begin full time on 8/13

6th Grade - Monday, August 10 (full time on 8/13)

7th Grade - Tuesday, August 11 (full time on 8/13)

8th Grade - Wednesday, August 12 (full time on 8/13)

Monday (8/10) - Freshman only at school

Tuesday (8/11) - Sophomores only at school

Wednesday (8/12) - Juniors and Seniors only at school

Thursday (8/13) - ALL students (9-12) at school

Anderson County Career & Technical Center
July 31 at 1:42 PM 路

We would like to welcome Mr. Jim Quick to the team at ACCTC. He will be the Criminal Justice Instructor on campus at ACCTC and at CHS. He brings a wealth of knowledge to the position. He is a 7 year veteran of the United States Marine Corps where he was a Combat Engineer. He has spent 26 years with the Knoxville Police Department on the Bomb Squad and Gang Task Force. He was the FBI Project Safe Neighborhoods Gang Task Force Officer of the Year, and is an in-service instructor for police officers at Walters State Community College. He is married to his wife Michelle and he has 3 children: Jeffrey, Kelsey, Paige and 3 Grand Children Alexys, Matt, Leighton.

post_text: We are excited to announce Rob Cummings as the new principal at Norris Middle School. Rob has worked in Anderson County Schools since 1999. He has taught reading, math, and science in and then transitioned to VP in 2007. Rob's accolades don't stop in the classroom. Rob has lead the Lady Senators basketball team to 3 TMSAA Large School Championships and 1 TMSAA Section Semi-Final, he also lead the boy's basketball team to 3 TMSAA Area Championships and 1 TMSAA AA Sectional Championships. Rob is married to his wife Christy and has 3 daughters. He love serving the students of the greater Norris Community. A lot of people are also asking, "Where is Mr. H.?" We are excited to announce that Mr. Harshbarger will be working with a select group of high school students to assist in an early graduation cohort and other hybrid learning programs. Congratulations to both these individuals. #EveryStudentEveryDay

June 24 at 4:42 PM 路

Its almost GRADUATION DAY!!! Here are a few friendly reminders:
1. Graduation practice is tomorrow (Thursday) 8:30 am.
2. Graduation tickets & programs will be handed out tomorrow after practice.
3. Each senior will receive 4 tickets.
4. Students must wear something school appropriate for graduation ceremonies under their gowns; no flip flops.
5. Guest temperatures will be taken before entering the football stadium.
6. Masks are recommended, but not required and will not be provided.
7. Seniors, report for graduation on Friday by 5:30 pm.

shared_text:
Clinton High School
June 1 at 3:42 PM 路

Real World Learning Experience...
Last June, the church Mr. Alderman attends was destroyed in a flood. During the rebuilding process, they decided to create a new church logo.

Mr. Alderman worked with Aaron Miller, a student in Mrs. Browns Digital Arts & Design program, to design and produce a new logo. The logo is now being used on the rebuilt church building.

A great example of our Career & Technical Education students gaining hands-on work experience while helping our community.

shared_text:
BBB Communications was live.
May 29 at 7:47 PM 路

This weeks Classic OEB Game of the Week will be from September 24, 2010 and will feature the Central Bobcats against the Clinton Dragons. It takes a goal line stand to win this game from ten years ago, be sure to tune in this weekend to watch every exciting minute of the action. Friday and Saturday night at 7pm right here on BBB TV-12 and of course you can watch it online on our website, BBBTV12.com, our Facebook Page, Our Twitter Page, and on our YouTube Channel. Or watch us on your Roku, Apple TV and FireStick devices by downloading the BoxCast channel and then looking for BBB TV-12. Weve posted video directions on our Facebook page and posted them to the top of the page on how to do this. We hope you enjoy these Classic and looking back at some of the games weve covered in the nearly 30 years of high school coverage on BBB TV-12.

May 28 at 8:21 AM 路

Are you moving into the area or have a child who is old enough to join Pre-K or Kindergarten? Its not too late to register your child! This cart is located right outside the front doors of the school. You can take the forms and fill them out and then place them on the next level of the cart. A staff member will pick them up during any business day.

Families, If you have any other work to turn in feel free to place it on the cart as well!

Have a great day!

#GOESKnows

post_text: The Anderson County School district is excited to announce Dan Jenkins as the new principal of Clinton High School. Dan has worked in our district for 15 years serving in multiple positions including: social studies teacher at CHS, boys and girls soccer and swimming coach, and multiple administrative roles. He started his professional career as a social studies teacher at Clinton High School before being asked to serve as a vice principal and athletic director for the Dragons. After serving at CHS, Dan was asked to be the principal at Norwood Middle School. Just last year, Norwood Middle was recognized by the Tennessee Department of Education as a Reward School. Dan is very excited to return to where his career started. He has always had a passion for both the academic and athletic success of his students. We are very excited to see the direction Dan takes the Dragons in the coming years. Currently, Dan lives in Clinton with his wife and 2 children.

To know these people is to love them! If they have inspired you, taught you something invaluable, or have just been plain awesome, let them know! You can use the comments to type your words of appreciation, share a memory, photo, sign, or video to give them a shout-out. Be creative!

Thank you to these amazing people for all you do! We hope you all feel loved and appreciated today!
